Manage the weg CLI tool and its system-level dependencies.

Examples:
  weg self install-tools   # Install devbox, direnv, etc
  weg self doctor          # Check system compatibility
  weg self update          # Update weg to latest version

Usage:
  weg self [command]

Available Commands:
  doctor        Check system setup and environment compatibility
  install-tools Install required tools (devbox, direnv, etc)
  update        Update weg to the latest version

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for self

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg self [command] --help" for more information about a command.
